  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed advertisement, by reason of its siting, design, and appearance, would comprise an incongruous and discordant feature to the shopfront, that would lead to less than substantial harm to the significance of the statutorily and locally listed building that would fail to be outweighed by any public benefit, and would fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the conservation area.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As such, the proposal would be contrary to p&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;olicies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;D3 and HC1 &lt;/span&gt;of the London Plan (2021) and policies &lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;LP1 (&lt;/span&gt;Design Quality and Local Character)&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;, LP3 (&lt;/span&gt;Designated Heritage Assets)&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;, and LP7 (&lt;/span&gt;Advertisements)  of the Hackney Local Plan LP33 (2020).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial, sans-serif; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;"
